cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.IT 

This paper is primarily focused on the networking aspects of SDN, specifically the scalability and reliability of the control plane. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for dynamically associating switches with controllers and devolving control of flows to switches, which involves distributed computing and control theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between costs and queue backlogs, which involves optimization and decision-making, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) possible categories. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of online algorithms, which involves theoretical computer science and algorithms, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
